text.__SUMMARY__:
Diospyros venosa is a tree in the family Ebenaceae. It grows up to 20 metres (70 ft) tall. Inflorescences bear up to 25 flowers. The fruits are ellipsoid to roundish, up to 2.5 cm (1 in) in diameter. The specific epithet venosa is from the Latin meaning "veined", referring to the leaf. Habitat is lowland mixed dipterocarp forests. D. venosa is found from Indochina to Malesia.
